cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the placement of unmanned aerial vehicle mounted base stations (UAV-BS) to provide network coverage to users. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The use of unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) in the proposed solution makes this paper relevant to the field of robotics. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the minimum required data rates per user, which is a concept related to information theory. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The placement of UAV-BSs can be seen as a control problem, where the objective is to maximize the number of covered users subject to certain constraints. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The proposed density-aware placement algorithm can be seen as an AI-based solution to the UAV-BS placement problem.
